Let me add on so you understand better.
If there is no smut, the next question is if the story is focused on romance first or a another genre.

I think the broader question isn't smut versus non-smut, but does the character progression lead to a sex scene or not.

My favorite tactic for fight scenes is to shorten up the average sentence. There is no upper limit on individuals, but I'm pretty generous with the 2-5 word sentences.

It helped me with my story, and I hope it helps you get a chapter and the whole thing done.

One of the weird things about English is that when we see a concept in another culture that we think is interesting, we borrow the locals' word for it. And if it was spelled using the Roman alphabet, we borrow the spelling, too, rather than attempting to render it using English phonemes. Our romanization of non-English scripts is a maze of contradictory systems that go in and out of fashion, too, and a word gets spelled in English with whatever romanization schema was in fashion at the moment, unless the author who yoinked the concept liked a different one, or tried to sound it out phonetically into English himself.
